questions.question_text:
What is the theoretical volume of carbon dioxide that can be obtained, at room temperature and pressure, when 1.2 g of  \( Na_{2}CO_{3}(s) \)  reacts with  \( 50\ cm^{3} \)  of 1.0 M  \( HNO_{3} \) ?
(Molar volume of gas at room temperature and pressure = 24 dm \( ^{3} \) ;

Relative atomic masses: H = 1.0, C = 12.0, N = 14.0, O = 16.0, Na = 23.0)
